{"id": "duc04-testb-1:8#26", "contents": "In exchange for these concessions, the players are seeking an increase in the minimum salary and the creation of an average salary exception. This would enable teams above the salary cap to sign one free agent per year for the average salary. The union's executive director, Billy Hunter, expressed optimism about the proposal, stating that the players made a valiant effort to reach an agreement. He emphasized that the players are not willing to accept a bad deal and are tired of the rhetoric and game-playing."}
